The server will receive a packet, read its id, instantiate a packet of the type corresponding to that id and then parse the remaining data filling its fields.
I thought of several ways to convert the id to a packet, but they all seemed bad to me.

**What I&#39;ve tried**

- A `Map&lt;Integer, Class&lt;? extends Packet&gt;&gt;` where each class gets registered with a different id and then instantiated on runtime with `map.get(id).newInstance()` (ignoring null checks). This works, but then I have to cast the packet to the corresponding packet type using a lot of instanceof

