Currency has one to many bidirectional association with Translation. The Translation table is used to localize both Type and Currency. The columns bound_to_id and bound_to_class indicate which entity the translation is for. There is no foreign key contstraint on bound_to_id and bound_to_class. There is a non-deferable unique constraint on the columns bound_to_id, bound_to_class and locale. (This is the reason I use bidirectional associations since upon say Type creation, Hibernate inserts Type, then inserts Translation with null bound_to_id and null bound_to_class which triggers the non-deferable constraint)

